      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1812_07_22_page01.jpg"/>
            <!--filenames for photos associated with this letter. Example: <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg image2.jpg image3.jpg"/> -->
            <opener>
               <dateline><!--If there's no date line, omit this element. Record in the order in which it is written on the letter.-->
                  <name type="place" ref="Id_where"/>
                  <date when="1812-07-22"/>July 22, 1812</dateline>
               <salute> To <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">Mrs. Miles</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1812_07_22_page02.jpg"/>
            <p> Dear Madam, with many<lb/> thanks for the trouble you<lb/> took in dressing our
               pretty<lb/> black lace gowns I now<lb/> send you the amount<lb/> of our debt <add>for
                  them</add>, which I believe<lb/> was £7. 10 — I have not the<lb/> letter in which
               the sum<lb/> was mentioned under<lb/> my hand &amp; if I should<lb/> have mistaken
               you will<lb/> have the goodness to set<lb/> me right —<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>May I further trouble<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1812_07_22_page03.jpg"/> you to try if you
               can<lb/> recollect whether you<lb/> sent black lace for the<lb/> bosom &amp; sleeves
               of <hi rend="underline">two</hi>
               <lb/> gowns or only of <hi rend="underline">one</hi>
               -<lb/> only two pieces of the broad<lb/> a yard &amp; three quarters, the narrow 3/4
                  Y<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>- —<lb/> reached us with the gowns<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I am Dear Madam<lb/> in hopes that <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX2">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.
                  Miles</persName>
               <lb/> will be prevailed upon<lb/> to make the excursion<lb/> my
               father has proposed<lb/> to him, and that we<lb/> shall have the pleasure of<lb/>
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1812_07_22_page04.jpg"/> seeing you both at<lb/>
               <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/tgn/1042937">Edgeworth Town</placeName>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs.</hi>
                  <lb/> Edgeworth</persName> joins
               heartily<lb/> in this wish with<lb/> Dear Madam<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer> Yours truly<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>July 24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1812<lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
            <!--You can include a <pb/> here, or inside the postScript.-->
